                <h1>Can Bad Credit Cause You to Fail a Background Check?</h1>
                <p>Yes, bad credit can lead to failing a background check. Employers and landlords often review your credit history to gauge reliability and financial responsibility. While not a definitive disqualifier, significant negative marks may raise concerns, particularly for positions involving financial responsibilities. It's essential to be aware of this when applying.</p>
